The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, Feb. 21: Bank of India (BoI) plans to raise up to $300 million through medium-term notes (MTN) in the first quarter of the next financial year to augment resources and fund international operations. ?Last week, the board approved a proposal to raise $1 billion from the international market by issuing MTNs in tranches,? a senior BoI official said.

 New Delhi, Feb. 21: The board of Hexaware Technologies Ltd has recommended a split of one share of face value Rs 10 to five units of face value Rs 2 each, the company informed the BSE today.

 New Delhi, Feb. 21: The National Organisation of Bank Workers today threatened to launch a nationwide agitation on February 25 to protest the merger of PSU banks as ?it will result in closure of branches and retrenchment of staff?.

 London, Feb. 21: Oil prices rose in London today, supported by fears that Opec could cut production next month, even amid colder weather in the US northeast and Europe, analysts said. In London, the price of Brent crude gained 65 cents to $46.99 a barrel in electronic dealing.

 Hong Kong, Feb. 21: Standard Chartered is looking to buy a consumer lending business in India, said Peter Sullivan, chief executive of the banks Hong Kong unit.




